This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of soccer ball detection using a convolutional neural network. Additionally, the paper also addresses the challenge of tracking the ball in an image sequence, which falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques for detection and tracking also suggests that the paper could be classified under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also presents empirical results to support the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of image sequences and spatio-temporal correlation suggests that the paper could also be classified under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
